[ ] QA 04: Constructors and Expanders
{@} @Local:7777<QA:Test.ConstructorsExpanders:1.0.0
   [@] @FS << @Community:filesystem<File.System:1.0.0

{-} -ProcessDirectories
   [ ] Output array declaration for processed items
   [ ] IO comes first
   [ ] ##Array is not a data type its a schema hence ##
   (-) >processedDirs##Array
      (>) #<type << #Folder
      (>) #<Dimensions << $$"1D"
   [T] -T.CLI"ProcessDirectories"
   [Q] -Q.Default
   [W] -W.Aljam3
   [ ]
   [ ] Define paths using constructors. Constructors are compile-time guaranteed.
   [ ] Another change is in place of $Path"..." 
   [ ] its $Folder"" or $File"" where the compiler
   [ ] even check if the string is folder or a file
   [ ] and that they exist - compile error otherwise.
   [-] $reportsPath << $Folder"/var/reports"
   [-] $logsPath << $Folder"/var/logs"
   [-] $archivesPath << $Folder"/var/archives"
   [ ]
   [ ] Initialize a 1D array of paths using Verbose Constructors and Constructor Input ($)
   [-] $dirArray##Array
      ($) #<ValueType << #Folder
      ($) #<Dimensions << $$"1D"
      ($) << $reportsPath
      ($) << $logsPath
      ($) << $archivesPath
   [ ]
   [ ] Use the unified expander to iterate over the array
   [=] =ForEach
      (=) <Data << $dirArray
      (=) >item >> $currentDir
      (=) >key >> $index
      [ ]
      [ ] Mini-pipeline per item
      [-] @FS-API.Directory.Create
         (-) <path << $currentDir
         (-) >status
            (>) >! $$"False"
      [ ]
      [ ] Collect paths back into a new array
      [*] *Collect
         (*) <item << $currentDir
         (*) <key << $index
         (*) >Array >> >processedDirs
